e=4 April 2020|website=ABC News|language=en-AU|access-date=4 April 2020}}</ref>\n*5 April: six men died in New South Wales (aged 91, 86, 85, 80, 76, and 61), three of whom had been passengers on the Ruby Princess,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2020-04-05/nsw-health-reports-four-more-coronavirus-deaths/12122966|title=Three Ruby Princess passengers among four more dead in NSW|last=Thomas|first=Sarah|date=5 April 2020|website=ABC News|language=en-AU|access-date=8 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"ABC06042020\">{{cite web|url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2020-04-06/coronavirus-death-toll-in-australia-rises-after-two-more-in-nsw/12123254?WT.ac=localnews_sydney|title=Sixth resident of Sydney nursing home dies of coronavirus as national tally rises to 41|website=ABC News|date=5 April 2020|accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>and one man in Queensland (aged 78) who had also been a passenger on the ''Ruby Princess''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2020-04-06/queenslands-coronavirus-weekend-what-we-did-wrong/12111900|title=Queensland's coronavirus weekend: What we got right and what we did wrong|last=Vonderen|first=Jessica van|date=6 April 2020|website=ABC News|language=en-AU|access-date=8 April 2020}}</ref>\n*6 April: There were two deaths in Victoria, a man in his 50s and a woman in her 80s,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2020-04-06/victoria-coronavirus-death-toll-rises-as-cases-increase/12124156|title=Man in his 50s becomes youngest person to die from coronavirus in Victoria|date=6 April 2020|website=ABC News|language=en-AU|access-date=8 April 2020}}</ref> a man in his 80s died in WA who was a passenger on the Ruby Princess<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2020-04-06/wa-fourth-coronavirus-death-at-royal-perth-hospital/12124280|title=Perth Ruby Princess passenger dies from coronavirus, taking WA toll to four|last=Kagi|first=Jacob|last2=Menagh|first2=Joanna|date=6 April 2020|website=ABC News|language=en-AU|access-date=8 April 2020}}</ref> and a 90-year-old man died at the Dorothy Henderson Lodge in Sydney, the sixth resident of the facility to die.<ref name=\"ABC06042020\" />\n*7 April: There were seven deaths, including the first to occur in South Australia, a 75-year-old man,<ref>{{cite web |title='Beloved father' is SA's first virus death |url=https://www.canberratimes.com.au/story/6714174/beloved-father-is-sas-first-virus-death/ |website=The Canberra Times |date=7 April 2020 |accessdate=7 April 2020}}</ref> two in WA, a man and a woman in their 70s,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2020-04-07/wa-coronavirus-deaths-rise-to-six-as-two-die-in-perth-hospitals/12128886|title='This disease can kill': Coronavirus claims two more lives in WA's deadliest day of outbreak|last=Kagi|first=Jacob|last2=Menagh|first2=Joanna|date=7 April 2020|website=ABC News|language=en-AU|access-date=8 April 2020}}</ref>a Tasmanian man in his 80s who was a passenger on the ''Ruby Princess'',<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2020-04-07/coronavirus-tasmania-third-death/12127782|title=Man in his 80s is Tasmanian's third coronavirus fatality|last=Hosier|first=Phoebe|date=7 April 2020|website=ABC News|language=en-AU|access-date=8 April 2020}}</ref> a man in his 90s and a woman in her 80s in New South Wales<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2020-04-07/nsw-coronavirus-social-distancing-to-stay-until-vaccine-found/12126802|title=NSW Premier says coronavirus social distancing to stay 'until vaccine is found'|last=Cockburn|first=Paige|date=7 April 2020|website=ABC News|language=en-AU|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=9 April 2020}}</ref> and a woman in her 80s died in Victoria.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dhhs.vic.gov.au/coronavirus-update-victoria-7-april-2020|title=Coronavirus update for Victoria - 7 April 2020|last=|first=|date=7 April 2020|website=Department of Health and Human Services Victoria|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=9 April 2020}}</ref>\n*8 April: There were two deaths, one in Victoria, a woman in her 80s,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dhhs.vic.gov.au/coronavirus-update-victoria-8-april-2020|title=Coronavirus update for Victoria - 8 April 2020|last=|first=|date=8 April 2020|website=Department of Health and Human Services Victoria|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=8 April 2020}}</ref> and 62-year-old SA woman who was a passenger on the ''Ruby Princess''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2020-04-08/south-australia-records-second-coronavirus-death/12131992|title=Adelaide woman dies after contracting coronavirus from Ruby Princess cruise ship|last=|first=|date=8 April 2020|website=ABC News|language=en-AU|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=8 April 2020}}</ref>\n*9 April: There was one death in SA, a 76-year-old man.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2020-04-09/south-australia-records-third-coronavirus-death/12135876|title=SA Premier urges everyone to 'be a good egg' and stay home as third coronavirus death recorded|last=|first=|date=9 April 2020|website=ABC News|language=en-AU|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=11 April 2020}}</ref>\n*10 April: There were three deaths, one in Victoria, a man in his 80s,<ref name=\":7\" /> one in New South Wales, a 69-year-old man,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2020-04-10/coronavirus-man-dead-as-increase-in-cases-steadies-in-nsw/12139586|title=Man, 69, dies from coronavirus overnight, NSW records 49 new cases|last=Elsworthy|first=Emma|date=10 April 2020|website=ABC News|language=en-AU|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=11 April 2020}}</ref>and a man in his 70s in Tasmania.<ref name=\":8\" />\n*11 April: There were two deaths. One was a man  in Victoria in his 80s, and a 91-year-old woman in New South Wales.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.health.nsw.gov.au/news/Pages/20200411_00.aspx |title=COVID-19 (Coronavirus) statistics |date